AB  - Existence of a Utility Function to Represent Preferences by T. Rader.In the above article in our October 1963 issue on p. 230, the definition of “aspiration set” should have read—“There is a finite set of points A called the aspiration set such that xRy if and only if there exists x′ɛA such that x ® x′ and x′Ry′ for all y′ɛA such that y ® y′.”It is regretted that on the cover of our April 1964 issue the name of K. Okuguchi was mis-spelt Ogukuchi and that A Reply to Professor Chang by Luigi L. Pasinetti on p. 106 of the same issue was not separately listed.
